wiki.content: On “Big Plans,” the members of Why Don’t We ask a girl to “take a chance” with them in a relationship. The song was released on the 17th of January, 2019, marking their first release after their debut album 8 Letters. The song was first teased by Why Don’t We when they posted a snippet of the song to their Instagram. Within 10 hours of this, the song was accidentally made available on Spotify for half an hour, predominately to Australian and New Zealand users. The first indication of the song’s release was when the band posted on their Instagram account on January 15, 2019. The post was a video filmed a month prior and contained audio from the song’s chorus. Prior to that, however, the band had already started referencing the song title in the caption of another post on December 21, 2018: “…We’re taking a little bit of a break from social media but don’t worry… we got BIG PLANS for 2019“ One day before the release of “Big Plans,” the band posted the following to their Instagram page: “We were hanging out in the back of the bus, driving through another state on our way to the next show and listening back to the mix of our next song. These are the moments we live for. A lot of the people in the industry have told us that we have to sound a certain way, or look a certain way in order to be successful but that’s not how we want to do things. We make music we love so we can share it with you. That’s what this song means to us. That’s what we’ve got planned this year for you…“ Read more on Last.fm.
